7f847781-c61e-46c0-aecf-6a972a756ca9.26e3cfaf-b85f-4998-b903-46add68719fe.description=
Synopsis

    This operator executes a command from the command line of a remote action server (RAS).

Inputs

    ipAddress - The IP address of the LIF (required).
    netMask - The net mask of the IP address (required).
    command - The command to execute.
    pyLibPath - 
    arguments - Any variables (data) to use in the command.
    environment - Specifies environment variables/values that need to be defined when running the command.
    path - The path to the command's executable file.
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

     cmd_timeout - Timeout in milliseconds before the command is considered failed when returnImmediately is false.
       Valid values\: Positive number miliseconds.
       Default value\: 100000 (100 seconds).

    returnImmediately - If true, the operation will execute the command and return immediately.  It will not wait for the command to finish.
       Valid values\: true, false.
       Default value\: false.

Results

    STDOUT - The standard output of the command.
    STDERR - The standard error output of the command.

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. On unix we cannot mandate what type of shell to be used (sh, bash, ksh, csh, etc), so be sure to include the shell in your command
         if you need things like file redirection.
           Example\:
           sh -c "ls -lha /etc > /tmp/myfile"
    2. On Windows, this command will prepend cmd.exe /C or command.exe /C to the command you specify, so there is no need to pass that into this operation.

7f847781-c61e-46c0-aecf-6a972a756ca9.7d2836dd-2a5d-48b9-aa67-3507cd10eef2.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults". As a result, the context key whose name is in the keyName input will be appended with the string from the input resultText.

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Returns\:
The the value of the context variable it appended to.

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

7f847781-c61e-46c0-aecf-6a972a756ca9.bb59306a-1c10-4b38-8354-8e90e2fccea4.description=
Synopsis

    This flow retrieves a group of export rules. Optional inputs restrict the search, if none are given, all export rules in the cluster are returned.
    getExportRules performs the following steps\:
      1. Pass the flow inputs in and assign the optional argument variables for the configuration.
      2. Call the remote action server (RAS) perl with the inputs.
      3. Validate the XML document from the RAS results.
      4. Query the XML document for the results. If the code is invalid, encode the invalid XML and set the reason for failure.
      5. If the code is valid, query the results for a status and determine that the status is passed. If it isn't passed, capture the reason for error.
      6. Pass the information to the requesting entity.

Inputs

   clusterName - The IP or host name of the NetApp cluster; specifies endpoint to run the API against (required).     
      Valid values\: Dot-decimal notation IPv4 address or RFC 1123 compliant host name.
      Default value\: None.

    vServerName - The name of the vServer used in the flow.
    policyName - The name of the policy.
    anon - 
    clientMatch - Interface dapts to match the client interface.
    chownMode - Changes the owner mode of the file path to own.
    exportNtfsUnixSecurityOps - The windows NT file system (NTFS) security operations.
    allowDev - Allow development of the export rules.
    allowSetUid - Allows a user to set the UID.
    roRule - 
    rwRule - Re-write an existing rule.
    superUser - A user who has access to all aspects of a system.
    ruleIndex - A list of rules.
    optArgVars- A query that specifies which  argument variables to return for the configuration (required).
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

    overrideJRAS - Value to override the system-defined Java RAS server.
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: Hosting Eng RAS.

Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow; in this case export policy rules.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. Example output (eg inputs were clusterName, vServerName, policyName)\:


        
                
                        65534
                        10.12.223.0/26
                        restricted
                        fail
                        true
                        true
                        S223000SL7VOL01
                        
                                nfs
                        
                        
                                sys
                        
                        1
                        
                                sys
                        
                        
                                sys
                        
                        S223000SL7NAS01
                
        
        1
